task.summary: Default task
Added sur_temperature to known libRadtran variables.
Added simple readOpenEXR() function to morticia.rad.radute.
Updates to Mitsuba doc.
Mitsuba doc updates.
Installation doc updates.
Update Mitsuba .rst.
Updated xd.py to use xarray.
Added information to installation.rst, mainly Mitsuba and Debian related.
Updates to installation.rst, mainly related to Mitsuba build on Debian 9 (Stretch).
morticia.rad.lirad now imports easygui only on demand. This is an attempt to stop ipyparallel engines from going into Qt-related blocking event loops. This may not be the cause of the problem.
Added run_dask_parallel() method to rad.librad.
Various doc additions and corrections. Added self.verbose property to librad.Case.
Updates to installation.rst. Mention of cesium.
Updates to mitsuba.st docs.
Updates to installation.rst.
Corrected input/output radiant units for Kato models, which is W rather than typically mW for other source solar files.
Used . instead of _ by mistake.
Added default filenames for librad.Case.
Start of morticia/mitusba integration module, called mortsuba to avoid masking of mistuba module.
Fixes to basic __init__ of Mitsuba object.
Added Transform class to mortsuba.py and start of Mitsuba class.
Methods to add REM and direct solar to Mitsuba scene. Basic testing.
Added function probe_mitsuba_SPECTRUM_SAMPLES. Seems to work on Windows and Linux.
Started adding Film class to mortusba. Animation transformations and reconstruction filters may not be accessible via Python, which would be a pity (particularly animations).
Added reconstruction filters and films as seperate classes in mortsuba.
Added many mortsuba classes for Mitsuba shapes, films, integrators, reconstruction filters etc.
Added Mitsuba shapes to mortsuba.
Started adding Mitsuba BSDFs in mortsuba.
Further additions of Mitsuba classes to mortsuba, including Spectrum and start of some textures.
Added more Mitsuba classes to mortsuba, including start of emitters.
Comments on MORTICIA architecture, 20151218.
Added more Mitsuba sensor classes to mortsuba.
Completed basic Mitsuba Sensor classes for mortsuba.
Added some docstrings from the Mitsuba manual.
Added another BSDF and some BASD docstrings.
Added thindielectric BSDF.
Added Shape disk and other Shape docstrings.
Added remainder of Shape docstrings in mortsuba.
Debugging and refactoring of mortsuba.py. Added render_local method. Some testing.
Debugging of mortsuba.py. Still have problems related to rendering jobs. If job name is not changed, same Mitsuba output as last is provided.
Work on integration of basic Mitusba rendering on local machine and getting numpy bitmaps.
Docstring for mortsuba.Scene.getBitmap.
Corrected mitsuba.rst on coordinate systems. Mitsuba is in fact right-handed (PBRT is left-handed). So MORTICIA is to be right-handed (+x east, +y north and +z zenith).
Corrections/additions to mitsuba.rst.
Corrections/additions to mitsuba.rst concerning coordinate frames etc.

Resumed work on morticia.rad.radute in the area of SpectralFunction, SpectralBasis and SpectralVector classes. Will try to subclass these to more general BasisFunction, FunctionalBasis and BasisVector respectively (in morticia.tools.xd).
Work on xd.py, Basis classes. Trouble with subtle bug in xd_product code.
Further progress on BasisFunction. Now discriminate uni-, bi- and multivariate cases in single class and constructor. Not sure this is the best approach.
Work on BasisFunction. If input samples are all np.nan, assume call evaluator directly.
